{"id":"food_cuisine_gen_077","q":"Which of these fruits is a true botanical berry?","a":"Banana","d":["Strawberry","Raspberry","Blackberry","Mulberry","Cherry","Fig"],"e":"True botanical berries must develop from a single flower with one ovary. Bananas qualify, as do grapes, tomatoes, and avocados. Strawberries are accessory fruits (flesh from the receptacle), and raspberries, blackberries, and mulberries are aggregate fruits. Cherries and figs are also not true berries.","l1":null,"l2":null,"i":"Removed 'Blueberry' and 'Watermelon' from distractors — both are true botanical berries and therefore wrong answers that were actually correct."}
